---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#081919] text-white">
    <Header />

    <main class="container mx-auto px-4 pt-28 pb-16 max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#02f1dc] mb-6">
        Purro Wallet – Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#b1cac4] mb-8">
        Effective date: 11/08/2025 · Contact: terrancrypt@gmail.com · Website:
        <a
          class="underline hover:text-white"
          href="https://purro.xyz"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">https://purro.xyz</a
        >
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">1) Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By installing or using the Purro Wallet browser extension (“Purro”,
          “we”, “our”, “Service”), you agree to these Terms of Service
          (“Terms”). If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">2) Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must be at least 18 years old and legally capable of entering into
          contracts. You represent that your use complies with applicable laws
          and that you are not subject to sanctions or restrictions that would
          prohibit use.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          3) Non‑Custodial Wallet; Your Responsibilities
        </h2>
        <p>
          Purro is a non‑custodial wallet. We do not hold, control, or recover
          your funds, seed phrase, or private keys.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are solely responsible for safeguarding your device, seed phrase,
          private keys, and password. Loss or compromise of these may result in
          irreversible loss of assets.
        </p>
        <p>
          You acknowledge that blockchain transactions are permanent and
          irreversible once confirmed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          4) No Financial/Investment Advice
        </h2>
        <p>
          Purro is a software tool. We do not provide investment, legal, tax, or
          financial advice. All actions you take using the Service are your own
          decisions and at your own risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">5) dApp and Third‑Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Purro enables you to connect to decentralized applications (dApps) and
          services (e.g., RPC providers, indexers, protocol APIs). These are not
          controlled by us.
        </p>
        <p>
          Interactions with third parties are governed by their own terms and
          privacy policies. We are not responsible for content, security,
          performance, availability, or outcomes of third‑party services.
        </p>
        <p>
          Network fees (gas) and third‑party fees may apply and are your
          responsibility.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          6) Software License and Restrictions
        </h2>
        <p>
          We grant you a limited, revocable, non‑exclusive, non‑transferable
          license to use the Service solely for its intended purpose as a Web3
          wallet.
        </p>
        <p>
          You agree not to: reverse engineer, modify, or create derivative works
          of the Service; use the Service for unlawful purposes; bypass
          security; or use automated means that may impair or disrupt the
          Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">7) Risks You Acknowledge</h2>
        <p>
          Using crypto and decentralized networks carries risks, including but
          not limited to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Loss of private keys/seed phrase, phishing, malware, device
            theft/compromise
          </li>
          <li>
            Smart contract bugs, protocol failures, forks, chain reorganizations
          </li>
          <li>Volatility, liquidity issues, and market risks</li>
          <li>RPC/provider downtime or data inaccuracies</li>
          <li>Regulatory changes affecting availability or legality</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You accept these risks and use the Service “as‑is”.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">8) Privacy and Data</h2>
        <p>
          See our Privacy Policy at
          <a
            class="underline hover:text-white"
            href="https://purro.xyz/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener">https://purro.xyz/privacy</a
          >. Purro does not custody your keys and does not execute remotely
          hosted code. When you use features (e.g., querying balances or
          broadcasting transactions), third‑party providers may process your IP
          and wallet address to fulfill the request.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">9) Updates and Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update the Service and these Terms at any time. Continued use
          after changes take effect constitutes acceptance. Material changes
          will be reasonably communicated (e.g., via website or extension
          listing).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">10) Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED “AS IS” AND “AS AVAILABLE” WITHOUT WARRANTIES
          OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION
          WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
          NON‑INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE
          ERROR‑FREE, SECURE, OR UNINTERRUPTED.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">11) Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, IN NO EVENT SHALL PURRO OR ITS
          CONTRIBUTORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL,
          CONSEQUENTIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR FOR ANY LOSS OF
          PROFITS, CRYPTOCURRENCY, DATA, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO
          YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH
          DAMAGES.
        </p>
        <p>
          TO THE EXTENT ANY LIABILITY ARISES, OUR AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT
          EXCEED THE GREATER OF (A) USD $100 OR (B) THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US (IF
          ANY) IN THE 12 MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">12) Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Purro, its affiliates, and
          contributors from any claims, damages, liabilities, costs, and
          expenses (including reasonable attorneys’ fees) arising from your use
          of the Service, your violation of these Terms, or your violation of
          any rights of a third party.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">13) Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may suspend or terminate your access to the Service at any time for
          any reason, including for violation of these Terms or applicable laws.
          Upon termination, provisions that by their nature should survive
          (e.g., disclaimers, limitations of liability) shall continue to apply.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          14) Governing Law; Dispute Resolution
        </h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of [Jurisdiction], without regard
          to conflicts of law principles.
        </p>
        <p>
          Disputes will be resolved in the courts of [Venue], unless otherwise
          required by law.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#b1cac4]">
          [Optional arbitration clause can be inserted here if desired.]
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">15) Prohibited Uses</h2>
        <p>
          You may not use the Service to: engage in unlawful activities; violate
          sanctions; launder money; finance terrorism; exploit minors;
          distribute malware; or infringe intellectual property or privacy
          rights.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">16) Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          We (or our licensors) retain all rights, title, and interest in and to
          the Service, including trademarks, logos, and software. No rights are
          granted except as expressly stated in these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">
          17) Severability; Entire Agreement
        </h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these Terms is deemed unenforceable, the remaining
          provisions shall remain in full force. These Terms constitute the
          entire agreement between you and us regarding the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">18) Contact</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>Legal entity: Terran Thai</li>
          <li>Email: terrancrypt@gmail.com</li>
          <li>Address: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[#b1cac4]">
          Notes: Blockchain transactions are irreversible and public. Always
          verify recipients, contracts, and dApps before signing.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
